17 (1) 'Dog' 'dog' means any domestic canine.
18 (2) 'Fighting related objects' means equipment, products, or materials of any kind that
19 are used, intended for use, or designed for use in the training, preparation, and
20 conditioning of a dog or game cock for fighting or for the furtherance of such act.
21 (3) 'Game cock' means a domesticated fowl that is bred, reared, or trained for the
22 purposes of fighting with other fowl.
23 (4) 'Minor' means any individual under the age of 18 years.
24 (b) Any person who:
25 (1) Owns, possesses, trains, transports, or sells any dog with the intent that such dog shall
26 be engaged in fighting with another dog;
27 (2) For amusement or gain, causes any dog to fight with another dog or for amusement
28 or gain, causes any dogs to injure each other;
29 (3) Owns, possesses, trains, transports, or sells any game cock with the intent that such
30 game cock shall be engaged in fighting with other fowl;
31 (4) For amusement or gain, causes any game cock to fight with other fowl or for
32 amusement or gain, causes any game cocks to injure each other;
33 (3)(5) Wagers money or anything of value on the result of such dogfighting dog or game
34 cock fighting;
35 (4)(6) Knowingly permits any act in violation of paragraph (1) or (2) of this subsection
36 on any premises under the ownership or control of such person or knowingly aids or abets
37 any such act; or
38 (5)(7) Knowingly promotes, or advertises, or charges an admission fee for an exhibition
39 of dog or game cock fighting with another dog
40 in violation of this subsection shall be guilty of a felony and, upon the first conviction
41 thereof, shall be punished by imprisonment of not less than one nor more than five years,
42 a fine of not less than $5,000.00, or both such fine and imprisonment. On a second or
43 subsequent conviction, such person shall be punished by imprisonment of not less than one
- 2 -

