44 nor more than ten years, a fine of not less than $15,000.00, or both such fine and
45 imprisonment. The court, as part of the sentence, may prohibit the offender from owning,
46 possessing, or exercising control over any animal within the species for which the
47 conviction is based. Each act in violation of this subsection shall constitute a separate
48 offense.
49 (c) Any person who is knowingly present only as a spectator or who causes or permits a
50 minor to be present at any place for the fighting of dogs or game cocks shall, upon a first
51 conviction thereof, be guilty of a misdemeanor of a high and aggravated nature. On a
52 second conviction, such person shall be guilty of a felony and shall be punished by
53 imprisonment of not less than one nor more than five years, a fine of not less than
54 $5,000.00, or both such fine and imprisonment. On a third or subsequent conviction, such
55 person shall be punished by imprisonment of not less than one nor more than ten years, a
56 fine of not less than $15,000.00, or both such fine and imprisonment. Each act in violation
57 of this subsection shall constitute a separate offense.
58 (d) Any dog or game cock subject to fighting may be impounded pursuant to the
59 provisions of Code Sections 4-11-9.2 through 4-11-9.6.
60 (e) Any person who knowingly possesses, purchases, or sells fighting related objects with
61 the intent that such objects be used in promoting, facilitating, training for, or otherwise
62 participating in an exhibition of dog or game cock fighting shall be guilty of a
63 misdemeanor of a high and aggravated nature.
64 (f) This Code section shall not prohibit, impede, or otherwise interfere with animal
65 husbandry, training techniques, competition, events, shows, or practices not otherwise
66 specifically prohibited by law and shall not apply to the following activities:
67 (1) Owning, using, breeding, training, or equipping any animal to pursue, take, hunt, or
68 recover wildlife or any animal lawfully hunted under Title 27 or participating in hunting
69 or fishing in accordance with the provisions of Title 27 and rules and regulations
