70 promulgated pursuant thereto as such rules and regulations existed on the date specified
71 in Code Section 27-1-39;
72 (2) Owning, using, breeding, training, or equipping dogs to work livestock for
73 agricultural purposes in accordance with the rules and regulations of the Commissioner
74 of Agriculture as such rules and regulations existed on January 1, 2008;
75 (3) Owning, using, breeding, training, or equipping dogs for law enforcement purposes;
76 or
77 (4) Owning, using, breeding, training, or equipping any animal to control damage from
78 nuisance or pest species in and around structures or agricultural operations."
79 SECTION 2.
80 Code Section 4-8-27 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to certificates of
81 registration, requirements for issuance of certificate, individuals excluded from receiving
82 registration, limitation of ownership, and annual renewal, is amended by revising
83 paragraph (2) of subsection (f) as follows:
84 "(2) The felony of dogfighting or game cock fighting as provided for in Code
85 Section 16-12-37 or the felony of aggravated cruelty to animals as provided for in Code
86 Section 16-12-4; or"
87 SECTION 3.
88 This Act shall become effective upon its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law
89 without such approval, and shall apply to all offenses committed on or after the effective date
90 of this Act.
91 SECTION 4.
92 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
